1998年5月13日，衣索比亞实施完全动员应对厄利垂亞發動的总体战攻势。<ref>The Eritrans describe the start of the war thus: "...after a series of armed incidents during which several Eritrean officials were murdered near the disputed village of Badme, Ethiopia declared total war as on 13 May and mobilized its armed forces for a full-scale assault on Eritrea." ({{cite web |author=Staff |title=history |publisher=Embassy of the State of Eritrea, New Delhi, India |url=http://www.eritreaembindia.com/history.htm |accessdate=August 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209041614/http://eritreaembindia.com/history.htm |archivedate=2015-02-09 }})</ref><ref name=bbc_total_war>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/107985.stm World: Africa Eritrea: 'Ethiopia pursues total war'] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/107985.stm |date=20200409000125 }}. [[BBC_News|BBC News]]. 6 June 1998.</ref>雖然兩國並未宣戰，但联合国安理会批准组建的衣索比亞-厄利垂亞赔偿委员会认为这证实了交战双方存在战争状态，衣索比亞也通知联合国安理会要求在联合国宪章第51条的权利。<ref>[http://www.pca-cpa.org/upload/files/FINAL%20ET%20JAB.pdf Jus Ad Bellum Ethiopia’s Claims 1–8] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pca-cpa.org/upload/files/FINAL%20ET%20JAB.pdf |date=20081031144656 }}(pdf) [http://www.pca-cpa.org/showpage.asp?pag_id=1151 Eritrea Ethiopia Claims Commission] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pca-cpa.org/showpage.asp?pag_id=1151 |date=20130112212535 }} Page 6. Paragraph 17 ([http://www.frompeacetojustice.nl/eCache/DEF/6/297.html A commentary on Eritrea Ethiopia Claims Commission findings)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.frompeacetojustice.nl/eCache/DEF/6/297.html |date=20071009095550 }}</ref>
